name: io.bytes.per.checksum
description:
The number of bytes per checksum.  Must not be larger than
  io.file.buffer.size.

name: dfs.datanode.block.id.layout.upgrade.threads
description:
The number of threads to use when creating hard links from
    current to previous blocks during upgrade of a DataNode to block ID-based
    block layout (see HDFS-6482 for details on the layout).

name: fs.s3a.threads.keepalivetime
description:
Number of seconds a thread can be idle before being
    terminated.

name: dfs.qjournal.write-txns.timeout.ms
description:
Write timeout in milliseconds when writing to a quorum of remote
    journals.

name: fs.s3a.retry.throttle.limit
description: Number of times to retry any throttled request.

name: dfs.datanode.max.transfer.threads
description:
Specifies the maximum number of threads to use for transferring data
        in and out of the DN.
